# QuickJobs Monorepo - Cursor AI Rules

## Tech Stack
- **Framework**: Next.js 14 (App Router)
- **Language**: TypeScript (strict mode)
- **UI**: React 18, Tailwind CSS, shadcn/ui
- **Build**: Turbo (monorepo)
- **Package Manager**: yarn
- **Localization**: Czech (UI text)

## Project Architecture

### Monorepo Structure
```
quickjobs/
├── apps/
│   ├── web-app/          # Main Next.js dashboard application
│   │   ├── app/          # App Router pages
│   │   ├── components/   # App-specific components
│   │   └── lib/          # App utilities
│   └── job-portal/       # Public job portal application
│       ├── app/          # App Router pages
│       ├── components/   # Portal-specific components
│       └── lib/          # Portal utilities
└── packages/
    ├── ui/               # Shared component library
    │   ├── src/components/  # Reusable UI components
    │   ├── src/hooks/       # Shared hooks
    │   └── src/lib/         # Shared utilities
    ├── eslint-config/    # Shared ESLint config
    └── typescript-config/ # Shared TS config
```

### Import Patterns
- **Within package**: Use relative imports (`./`, `../`)
- **Cross-package**: Use absolute imports (`@ui/components`, `@ui/hooks`)
- **Import order**: 
  1. React/Next.js imports
  2. Third-party libraries
  3. Local imports (components, hooks, utils)
  4. Type imports (use `import type { ... }` when possible)
- **Path aliases**: Configured in `tsconfig.json` (e.g., `@ui/*` → `packages/ui/src/*`)

## TypeScript Guidelines

### Type Safety
- **Never use `any`** - use `unknown` if type is truly unknown, then narrow with type guards
- **Explicit return types** - Always define return types for functions (except simple arrow functions where inference is obvious)
- **Interfaces vs Types**: 
  - Use `interface` for object shapes and component props
  - Use `type` for unions, intersections, and computed types
- **Utility types**: Leverage `Partial<T>`, `Pick<T, K>`, `Omit<T, K>`, `Record<K, V>`, etc.
- **Type imports**: Use `import type { ... }` for type-only imports

### Examples
```typescript
// ✅ Good
interface UserProps {
  name: string;
  age: number;
  onUpdate: (data: Partial<UserProps>) => void;
}

function processUser(data: unknown): UserProps {
  if (typeof data === 'object' && data !== null) {
    // Type guard
    return data as UserProps;
  }
  throw new Error('Invalid user data');
}

// ✅ Type-only import
import type { User } from './types';

// ❌ Avoid
const handleData = (data: any) => { }
function getValue() { return fetch(...) } // Missing return type
```

## Component Patterns

### Component Structure
```typescript
"use client"; // Only if client component needed

import { useState } from "react";
import type { ComponentNameProps } from "./types";

export const ComponentName = ({ 
  title, 
  onAction 
}: ComponentNameProps) => {
  const [state, setState] = useState("");

  return (
    <div className="flex flex-col gap-4">
      <h2>{title}</h2>
    </div>
  );
};
```

### Component Guidelines
- **Default**: Server Components (no "use client" directive)
- **Client Components**: Only add `"use client"` when:
  - Using React hooks (`useState`, `useEffect`, etc.)
  - Using browser APIs (`window`, `document`, `localStorage`, etc.)
  - Handling events (`onClick`, `onChange`, etc.)
  - Using context providers/consumers
- **Naming**: 
  - PascalCase for components (`JobCard`, `UserProfile`)
  - camelCase for utilities and hooks (`formatDate`, `useAuth`)
  - kebab-case for file names (`job-card.tsx`, `user-profile.tsx`)
- **Exports**: Always use named exports (`export const Header = () => {}`)
- **No FC/React.FC**: Type props inline in function parameters, not with `React.FC`
- **Props destructuring**: Destructure props in function signature
- **Optimization**: 
  - Use `React.memo()` for expensive renders
  - Use `useMemo()` for expensive calculations
  - Use `useCallback()` for stable function references passed to memoized children

### File Naming
- Components: `ComponentName.tsx` (PascalCase)
- Utilities: `utility-name.ts` (kebab-case)
- Hooks: `use-hook-name.ts` (kebab-case with `use-` prefix)
- Types: `types.ts` or `component-name.types.ts`

## Next.js App Router

### File Conventions
- `page.tsx` - Route page component (required for route)
- `layout.tsx` - Shared layout wrapper (persists across navigation)
- `loading.tsx` - Loading UI with Suspense (automatic)
- `error.tsx` - Error boundary (catches errors in route segment)
- `not-found.tsx` - 404 page (custom not found UI)
- `route.ts` - API endpoint handler
- `template.tsx` - Template component (re-renders on navigation)

### Dynamic Routes
- `[id]/` - Single dynamic segment
- `[id]/[slug]/` - Multiple dynamic segments
- `[...slug]/` - Catch-all segment (matches all paths)
- `[[...slug]]/` - Optional catch-all (matches including root)

### Route Handlers (API Routes)
```typescript
// app/api/jobs/route.ts
import { NextRequest, NextResponse } from "next/server";

export async function GET(request: NextRequest) {
  const searchParams = request.nextUrl.searchParams;
  const id = searchParams.get("id");
  
  // Fetch data
  const data = await fetchJobs(id);
  
  return NextResponse.json({ data });
}

export async function POST(request: NextRequest) {
  try {
    const body = await request.json();
    
    // Validate and process
    const result = await createJob(body);
    
    return NextResponse.json({ success: true, data: result }, { status: 201 });
  } catch (error) {
    return NextResponse.json(
      { error: "Nepodařilo se vytvořit nabídku" },
      { status: 500 }
    );
  }
}
```

### Middleware
```typescript
// middleware.ts
import { NextResponse } from "next/server";
import type { NextRequest } from "next/server";

export function middleware(request: NextRequest) {
  // Auth check, redirects, headers, etc.
  const token = request.cookies.get("token");
  
  if (!token && request.nextUrl.pathname.startsWith("/dashboard")) {
    return NextResponse.redirect(new URL("/login", request.url));
  }
  
  return NextResponse.next();
}

export const config = {
  matcher: ["/dashboard/:path*", "/api/protected/:path*"],
};
```

### Environment Variables
- Use `NEXT_PUBLIC_` prefix for client-side variables
- Access via `process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL`
- Server-only variables: `process.env.API_SECRET` (no prefix)
- Type safety: Create `env.d.ts` for type definitions

## Styling with Tailwind

### Best Practices
- **Utility Classes**: Use Tailwind utilities, avoid inline styles
- **shadcn/ui**: Leverage component patterns and variants
- **Theming**: Use CSS variables for theming (`bg-background`, `text-foreground`)
- **Responsive**: Mobile-first approach (`sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`, `xl:`)
- **Utility Order**: Group logically - layout → spacing → typography → colors → effects
- **Conditional Classes**: Use `cn()` utility for conditional classes
  ```typescript
  import { cn } from "@ui/lib/utils";
  
  <div className={cn(
    "flex flex-col gap-4",
    isActive && "bg-primary",
    className // Allow override
  )}>
  ```

### Example
```typescript
<div className="flex flex-col gap-4 p-6 rounded-lg bg-background border border-border">
  <h2 className="text-2xl font-semibold text-foreground">
    Nadpis
  </h2>
  <p className="text-sm text-muted-foreground">
    Popis
  </p>
</div>
```

### Common Patterns
```typescript
// Container with max-width
<div className="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">

// Flex layouts
<div className="flex items-center justify-between gap-4">

// Grid layouts
<div className="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4">

// Responsive text
<h1 className="text-2xl sm:text-3xl lg:text-4xl font-bold">

// Hover states
<button className="hover:bg-accent hover:text-accent-foreground transition-colors">
```

## Shared UI Package

### Usage
```typescript
// Import shared components from core or specific folders
import { Button } from "@ui/components/core/button";
import { Dialog } from "@ui/components/core/dialog";
import { Input } from "@ui/components/core/input";
import { useToast } from "@ui/hooks/use-toast";
import { cn } from "@ui/lib/utils"; // className utility
```

### Creating Shared Components
- **Atomic Design**: Keep components small and focused
- **Reusability**: Accept common HTML attributes via spread props
  ```typescript
  interface ButtonProps extends React.ButtonHTMLAttributes<HTMLButtonElement> {
    variant?: "default" | "destructive" | "outline";
    size?: "sm" | "md" | "lg";
  }
  ```
- **TypeScript Generics**: Use for flexible component APIs
  ```typescript
  interface SelectProps<T> {
    value: T;
    onChange: (value: T) => void;
    options: Array<{ label: string; value: T }>;
  }
  ```
- **shadcn/ui Patterns**: Follow established patterns (variants, compound components)
- **Composition**: Prefer composition over configuration
- **Accessibility**: Include proper ARIA attributes and keyboard navigation

## Czech Localization

### Guidelines
- **UI Text**: All user-facing text in Czech
- **Code**: Variables, functions, comments in English
- **Error Messages**: User-visible errors in Czech
- **Types/Interfaces**: English names

### Example
```typescript
interface JobFormProps {
  onSubmit: (data: JobData) => void;
}

export const JobForm = ({ onSubmit }: JobFormProps) => {
  return (
    <form>
      <label>Název pozice</label>
      <button type="submit">Uložit nabídku</button>
    </form>
  );
};
```

## State Management

### Local State
- **Simple State**: Use `useState` for primitive values and simple objects
  ```typescript
  const [count, setCount] = useState(0);
  const [user, setUser] = useState<User | null>(null);
  ```
- **Complex State**: Use `useReducer` for state machines or complex logic
  ```typescript
  type State = { count: number; step: number };
  type Action = { type: "increment" } | { type: "decrement" } | { type: "reset" };
  
  const reducer = (state: State, action: Action): State => {
    switch (action.type) {
      case "increment": return { ...state, count: state.count + state.step };
      case "decrement": return { ...state, count: state.count - state.step };
      case "reset": return { ...state, count: 0 };
    }
  };
  
  const [state, dispatch] = useReducer(reducer, { count: 0, step: 1 });
  ```
- **State Lifting**: Lift state only when multiple components need it
- **Context**: Use React Context for deeply nested prop drilling (avoid overuse)

### Server State
- **Prefer Server Components**: Fetch data in Server Components when possible
- **Caching**: Use `fetch` with Next.js automatic caching
- **Revalidation**: 
  - `revalidatePath("/jobs")` - Revalidate specific path
  - `revalidateTag("jobs")` - Revalidate by tag
  - `revalidateTime` - Time-based revalidation

### Custom Hooks
```typescript
// hooks/use-jobs.ts
import { useState, useEffect } from "react";

export function useJobs() {
  const [jobs, setJobs] = useState<Job[]>([]);
  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(true);
  const [error, setError] = useState<string | null>(null);

  useEffect(() => {
    async function fetchJobs() {
      try {
        setLoading(true);
        const res = await fetch("/api/jobs");
        if (!res.ok) throw new Error("Failed to fetch");
        const data = await res.json();
        setJobs(data);
      } catch (err) {
        setError(err instanceof Error ? err.message : "Unknown error");
      } finally {
        setLoading(false);
      }
    }
    
    fetchJobs();
  }, []);

  return { jobs, loading, error, refetch: fetchJobs };
}
```

## Error Handling

### Error Boundaries (Client)
```typescript
// app/error.tsx
"use client";

import { useEffect } from "react";
import { Button } from "@ui/components/core/button";

export default function Error({
  error,
  reset,
}: {
  error: Error & { digest?: string };
  reset: () => void;
}) {
  useEffect(() => {
    // Log to error reporting service
    console.error("Error:", error);
  }, [error]);

  return (
    <div className="flex flex-col items-center justify-center min-h-screen gap-4">
      <h2 className="text-2xl font-semibold">Něco se pokazilo</h2>
      <p className="text-muted-foreground">
        {error.message || "Došlo k neočekávané chybě"}
      </p>
      <Button onClick={reset}>Zkusit znovu</Button>
    </div>
  );
}
```

### Server-Side Error Handling
```typescript
// app/api/jobs/route.ts
import { NextResponse } from "next/server";

export async function GET() {
  try {
    const data = await fetchJobs();
    return NextResponse.json({ data });
  } catch (error) {
    console.error("API Error:", error);
    return NextResponse.json(
      { error: "Nepodařilo se načíst nabídky" },
      { status: 500 }
    );
  }
}
```

### Async Component Error Handling
```typescript
// app/jobs/page.tsx
export default async function JobsPage() {
  try {
    const jobs = await getJobs();
    return <JobList jobs={jobs} />;
  } catch (error) {
    // This will trigger error.tsx
    throw new Error("Nepodařilo se načíst nabídky");
  }
}
```

### Form Error Handling
```typescript
"use client";

import { useState } from "react";

export const JobForm = () => {
  const [error, setError] = useState<string | null>(null);
  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(false);

  const handleSubmit = async (e: React.FormEvent) => {
    e.preventDefault();
    setError(null);
    setLoading(true);
    
    try {
      await createJob(formData);
    } catch (err) {
      setError(err instanceof Error ? err.message : "Chyba při ukládání");
    } finally {
      setLoading(false);
    }
  };

  return (
    <form onSubmit={handleSubmit}>
      {error && <div className="text-destructive">{error}</div>}
      {/* form fields */}
    </form>
  );
};
```

## Performance

### Optimization Checklist
- **Server Components**: Use by default (no client JS unless needed)
- **Code Splitting**: Use dynamic imports for heavy components
  ```typescript
  const HeavyComponent = dynamic(() => import("./HeavyComponent"), {
    loading: () => <LoadingIndicator />,
    ssr: false, // Only if component requires browser APIs
  });
  ```
- **Images**: Always use `next/image` with proper sizing
  ```typescript
  <Image
    src="/logo.png"
    alt="Logo"
    width={200}
    height={100}
    priority // For above-the-fold images
  />
  ```
- **Loading States**: Use `loading.tsx` for instant loading UI
- **Error Boundaries**: Implement at route level with `error.tsx`
- **Memoization**: 
  - `useMemo()` for expensive calculations
  - `useCallback()` for stable function references
  - `React.memo()` for component memoization
- **Debouncing**: Use for search inputs, form validation
  ```typescript
  import { useDebouncedValue } from "@ui/hooks/use-debounce";
  
  const [debouncedSearch] = useDebouncedValue(searchTerm, 300);
  ```
- **Streaming**: Use Suspense boundaries for progressive loading
  ```typescript
  <Suspense fallback={<LoadingIndicator />}>
    <AsyncComponent />
  </Suspense>
  ```
- **Bundle Size**: 
  - Import only what you need (`import { Button }` not `import *`)
  - Use tree-shaking friendly imports
  - Analyze bundle with `@next/bundle-analyzer`

## Git Commit Convention

### Format
```
type(scope): description

[optional body]

[optional footer]
```

### Types
- `feat` - New feature
- `fix` - Bug fix
- `docs` - Documentation changes
- `style` - Code style (formatting, semicolons)
- `refactor` - Code refactoring
- `perf` - Performance improvements
- `test` - Adding/updating tests
- `chore` - Maintenance tasks
- `ci` - CI/CD changes

### Examples
```bash
feat(dialog): přidání auto-save do formulářů nabídek
fix(auth): oprava refreshe tokenu při expiraci
refactor(ui): zjednodušení props u Button komponenty
perf(jobs): optimalizace načítání seznamu nabídek
chore(deps): aktualizace Next.js na verzi 14.1
docs(readme): doplnění deployment instrukce
```

### Scope Guidelines
- `ui` - UI package changes
- `auth` - Authentication
- `api` - API routes
- `dialog` - Dialog components
- `form` - Form components
- Component/feature name

### Breaking Changes
```bash
feat!: odstranění deprecated API endpointu

BREAKING CHANGE: API endpoint /api/old byl odstraněn, 
použijte /api/v2/new
```

## Code Generation Preferences

### When Generating Code
1. **TypeScript**: Always use explicit types, avoid `any`
2. **Server First**: Prefer Server Components unless interactivity needed
3. **Error Handling**: Always include try/catch for async operations
4. **Localization**: Czech for UI text, English for code/comments
5. **File Naming**: Follow conventions strictly (kebab-case for files, PascalCase for components)
6. **Loading States**: Always implement loading states for async operations
7. **Documentation**: Add JSDoc comments for complex functions and public APIs
8. **Styling**: Use Tailwind utilities, avoid inline styles and custom CSS
9. **Accessibility**: Include proper ARIA labels and semantic HTML
10. **Performance**: Consider memoization, code splitting, and bundle size

### Code Quality Checklist
- ✅ TypeScript strict mode compliance
- ✅ Proper error boundaries and error handling
- ✅ Loading and empty states
- ✅ Responsive design (mobile-first)
- ✅ Accessibility (keyboard navigation, ARIA)
- ✅ Performance optimizations (memo, dynamic imports)
- ✅ Czech localization for user-facing text
- ✅ Consistent code style and formatting

## Async/Await Patterns

### Error Handling
```typescript
// ✅ Good - Explicit error handling
async function fetchData(): Promise<Data> {
  try {
    const res = await fetch("/api/data");
    if (!res.ok) throw new Error(`HTTP ${res.status}`);
    return await res.json();
  } catch (error) {
    console.error("Failed to fetch data:", error);
    throw error; // Re-throw or handle appropriately
  }
}

// ❌ Avoid - Silent failures
async function fetchData() {
  const res = await fetch("/api/data");
  return res.json(); // No error handling
}
```

### Parallel Requests
```typescript
// ✅ Good - Parallel fetching
const [jobs, users, stats] = await Promise.all([
  fetchJobs(),
  fetchUsers(),
  fetchStats(),
]);

// ✅ Good - With error handling
const results = await Promise.allSettled([
  fetchJobs(),
  fetchUsers(),
  fetchStats(),
]);
```

### Sequential with Dependencies
```typescript
// ✅ Good - Sequential when dependent
const user = await fetchUser(id);
const jobs = await fetchUserJobs(user.id);
```

